<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN335">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>aṭalarun tuppiṉ............</l>
<l>.........................kuruntē mullai yeṉ</l>
<l>ṟinnāṉ kallatu pūvu millai</l>
<l>karuṅkāl varakē yiruṅkatirt tiṉaiyē</l>
<l>ciṟukoṭik koḷḷē poṟikiḷa ravaraiyo</l>
<l>ṭinnāṉ kalla tuṇāvu millai</l>
<l>tuṭiyaṉ pāṇaṉ paṟaiyaṉ kaṭampaṉeṉ</l>
<l>ṟinnāṉ kallatu kuṭiyu millai</l>
<l>yoṉṉāt tevvar muṉṉiṉṟu vilaṅki</l>
<l>yoḷiṟēntu maruppiṟ kaḷiṟeṟintu vīḻnteṉak</l>
<l>kallē paravi ṉallatu</l>
<l>nellukuttup paravuṅ kaṭavuḷu milavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Of a strength difficult to kill….</l>
<l>…………..the wild line and the jasmine,</l>
<l>apart from these four there is no [other] flower,</l>
<l>the black-stalked millet, the large-eared miller,</l>
<l>the little horse-gram along with the spotted field bean,</l>
<l>apart from these four there is no [other] food,</l>
<l>and the Tuṭi drummer, the bard, the Paṛai drummer and the Kaṭampaṉ,</l>
<l>apart from these four there is no [other] clan.</l>
<l>Because he fell after standing in front of the disagreeing enemies [and] blocking [them], </l>
<l>having attacked an elephant bull with resplendent eminent tusks,</l>
<l>except if one worships the very stone</l>
<l>there are no [other] gods that are worshipped by scattering paddy.</l>  
</lg>
    </div>
